{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSButton"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions"]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Appearances","anchor":"Appearances","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Five appearances are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default (by default)"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"brand","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": A brand primary color alternative to the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" button.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A button with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Brand"},{"text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"minimal"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A button with ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSButton.Appearance.Negative","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" appearance is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default appearance","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\", appearance: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), accessibilityLabel: \"Like\") { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", appearance: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong appearance and button taking full width","    OUDSButton(text: \"Validate\", icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), appearance: .strong, isFullWidth: true) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSButton(LocalizedStringKey(\"validate_button\"), bundle: Bundle.module, appearance: .strong) { }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSButton(text: \"Button\",","               icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","               flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Styles","text":"Styles","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Two style are available:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"disabled","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"pressed","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"hovered","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" or normal (i.e. "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"enabled","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"loading","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Rounded-layout","text":"Rounded layout","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedButtons"},{"text":" values of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Tuning","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" object"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in your theme configuration (if the theme exposes this property at init)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Some themes do not have this flexibility like ","type":"text"},{"code":"SoshTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"WireframeTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Colored-surface","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Colored surface"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If button is placed on colored surface using ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface."}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Specific-behavior","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Specific behavior"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-button","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering"},{"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange Compact"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_OrangeCompact"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Sosh","text":"Sosh","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Wireframe"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_button_Wireframe"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Version","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3.2.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Since","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.10.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(_:tableName:bundle:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton\/init(_:tableName:bundle:icon:flipIcon:appearance:style:isFullWidth:action:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\